local a = false
local smallball = game.Workspace.smallball
local function PARTOUCHED3(otherPart)
	if a == false then
		a = true
		smallball.BrickColor = BrickColor.new("Bright red")
		task.wait(3)
		smallball.BrickColor = BrickColor.new("Medium stone grey")
		a = false
	end
end

smallball.Touched:connect(PARTOUCHED3)
[[--This the code for a ball turning red and returning it back to the same color after 3 seconds
In this code we are using events where the parameter - 'otherPart'(which is any part in the game) connects the small ball.
we took the variable a and set to false and smallblock which is the reference to the ball in the game.
We took the function 'PARTOUCHED3' with the parameter otherPart to fire this event.
This peice of code - 	'if a == false then
		a = true
		smallball.BrickColor = BrickColor.new("Bright red")
		task.wait(3)
		smallball.BrickColor = BrickColor.new("Medium stone grey")
		a = false
	end
end',
states that when a == false,
1.it sets a to true
2.sets the ball to red for 3 seconds
3.returns it back to its original color
4.and sets a back to false again
The purpose for this code is to create a debounce where the ball will only turn red and return back to its original color if - 'if a == false then..' is fired.
And in order to fire - 'if a == false...' , the player has to touch the ball.
So ultimately it creates a debounce effect.
And the - 'smallball.Touched:connect(PARTOUCHED3) is the event that conencts to the function PARTOUCHED3 and operates with the parameter - 'otherPart'
